The High Court in Pretoria will today hear an application to interdict Eskom from cutting power to eight municipalities PRETORIA - Civil rights group AfriForum wants Eskom to stick to the agreement reached last year and not disconnect non-paying municipalities until the courts have ruled on the constitutionality of such disconnections.The High Court in Pretoria will on Wednesday hear an application to interdict Eskom from cutting power to eight municipalities in the Free State, North West and Northern Cape.AfriForum s Willie Spies says Eskom should hold off on disconnecting municipalities until its main application is heard. Spies says law-abiding ratepayers shouldn t be punished because of their poorly managed municipalities.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)